FT  26 OCT 94 / China announces infrastructure spending costs
China's spending on infrastructure would be about Dollars 500bn (Pounds
316bn) over the next decade, Mr Liu Zhongli, the country's finance minister,
told an Asian Development Bank-sponsored conference in Beijing, writes Tony
Walker. Mr Liu said that to meet China's huge requirements more funds would
be raised internationally, either through bond issues or from loans provided
by international financial institutions and foreign governments.
